properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 1:40PM MST until February 13 at 12:00AM MST by NWS Pueblo CO
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches.
Snowfall will be highly variable in intensity with rapidly
deteriorating conditions possible over short distances.

* WHERE...Teller, Northern El Paso, and Northern Fremont Counties,
and the Wets and Sangre De Cristo mountains.

* WHEN...Until midnight MST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions which will be
deteriorating during the evening commute, especially across
Northern El Paso and Teller counties.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT MST TONIGHT
